In a new interview with 1843, Donatella Versace says the brand will no longer carry fur. “Fur? I am out of that. I don’t want to kill animals to make fashion. It doesn’t feel right,” she said. Donatella is the creative director of the brand. Rabbit pillow and a Camel coat with mink lapels are some of the items you can buy on the online store versace.com. Fur has been seen on the runway as recently as the fall 2018 collection in Milan this February. We’re guessing Donatella isn’t too concerned over this discrepancy: “Versace needs to mean change,” she said later in the interview. Read More: Why Do Trousers Have A Tiny Pocket That’s Too Small To Use? Read More: Nugo Udoye: Pimping Cars To Die For